<plot>Most likely a disappointing film for those who, for whatever reason, rate Joseph Losey among the exalted directors or think Paul Muni was not capable of over-acting, the two-pronged story concerns a nameless, homeless and rejected man (Paul Muni) who is looking for a new life, and a young boy (Vittorio Manunta) from an impoverished family, who is forced to steal when he loses the milk money. The man accidently kills a woman, and the two come together in the same hiding place.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?260741</url></doc>
